    "content": "Done. Read the translator's full memo and appended editorial notes to my Memo.md under \"## Translator's Memo Notes (editorial extraction).\"\n\nKey takeaways:\n\n1. **The translator and I are fully aligned** on registers (same 5 identified independently), structural principles (map directly to my hard boundaries), and terminology (same glossary).\n\n2. **11 specific items I'll track during editing**: first-occurrence glossing, classical quotation formatting, \"phenomenal X\" prefix enforcement, re-glossing at register transitions, the 德 split convention, 诗意 capitalization, Essay 2 footnote integration, the meme replacement effect, 虚妄 disambiguation footnote, and the 形=现象 reinterpretation note.\n\n3. **Essay 2 as register calibrator**: The translator notes Essay 2's analytic voice serves as the register standard for analytic passages. Useful for editing calibration.\n\n4. **No conflicts found** between the translator's approach and my editorial constraints. We are ready to work on drafts in parallel."
